                            Severus wrote a letter to 
                            Andrew concerning 
                            the holy virgins,
                            free women, and the death of 
                            Zosimus. 
                            
                                
                            
                         <a href="/3142-1" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span>
                                <span class="tei-persName">Prosdocia</span>
                                was a martyr.
                             <a href="/3141-10" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">Dioscorus</span> was a martyr. <a href="/3142-10" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">Euphemia</span> was a martyr. <a href="/804-10" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span>
                                <span class="tei-persName">Berenice</span>
                                was a martyr.
                             <a href="/3141-11" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">
                                    Ignatius </span> was a martyr.  <a href="/3116-12" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">
                                    Cyrprian </span> was a martyr.  <a href="/3111-14" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>
                            Sometime during the episcopacy of Severus of Antioch
                             Eutychian  the governor of 
                             Apamea  joined in celebrating martyrs and dedicating a church with 
                            Anonymous 3740 despite the fact that he had lawfully deprived of his priestly office.
                         <a href="/3083-16" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName"> John </span> was saint and a martyr. <a href="/816-21" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">Peter</span> was a martyr. <a href="/3142-24" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">
                                    Polycarp </span> was a martyr.  <a href="/3116-25" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">
                                    Dioscorus </span> was a martyr.  <a href="/3099-26" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>Severus
                            encouraged Solon to live a holy and virtuous life, modelling the
                            piety of Jesus
                            andthe martyrs, especially Thecla, so that the
                            legitimacy of his ordination by a bishop outside of the diocese might be
                            confirmed.  <a href="/3012-30" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">Judas</span> was a martyr. <a href="/3142-31" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">Leontius</span> was a martyr. <a href="/3142-37" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">Thomas</span> was a martyr.  <a href="/818-4" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">sanctity: </span><span class="tei-persName">Paul</span> was a martyr. <a href="/816-5" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>Addai and
                                Abraham
